<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09100e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09100e">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09100e"> 100(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 40 hours / 36 days / 40 days</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>By the Way</b> The period at which the fast of Ash Wednesday was instituted is uncertain, but we do know that in the Latin Church Lent formerly lasted but <mark>thirty-six days</mark>. It was in the fifth century that four days were added in imitation of the <mark>forty days</mark> fast of the Saviour, and this usage has been maintained ever since. <small> <a name="FJ5mar24" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FJ5mar24"><cite title="source">Freeman's Journal</cite></a> (5 March 1924) 8/5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
